The paper deals with computer vision techniques applied to artworks, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper proposes a novel architecture for image-to-image translation, which involves learning from real photos and leveraging a weakly-supervised semantic understanding of the scene, indicating that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also mentions the improvement in performance of pre-trained architectures for classification, detection, and segmentation, which suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR), multimedia (cs.MM), or machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
